# Documentation Requirements for Cloakyard

1. **Next.js Code Fixes (`guidetomake.md`)**:
   - ANY time a Next.js bug is fixed, a new feature is added, or a file is changed, you MUST automatically append a new entry to the Developer Log in `C:\Users\amish\.gemini\antigravity\brain\cbb1aaa9-18b3-418c-8995-b118e52c5374\guidetomake.md`.
   - The entry MUST include: The exact file changed, what problem it was causing, how the error was spotted (terminal commands/logic), and exactly how the code was fixed.
   - Do this proactively. Do not wait for the user to ask.

2. **WooCommerce Steps (`STEVEN.html`)**:
   - ANY time a new WooCommerce mechanic is introduced (e.g., handling variable prices, attributes, stock, tags), you MUST automatically update `C:\Users\amish\.gemini\antigravity\brain\cbb1aaa9-18b3-418c-8995-b118e52c5374\STEVEN.html`.
   - Ensure it is written as a step-by-step master guide for the user to follow in their Hostinger dashboard.
   - Do this proactively. Do not wait for the user to ask.
